From 62deb0b774aa8ceaa907be23d52044d3838470aa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 19:24:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add leakage-free holdout validation and recency weighting for
 the train->test shift
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The station time-profiles alone did not move the leaderboard because the model
could already recover them from the raw features, and — more importantly —
because the real bottleneck is the winter->spring distribution shift between the
training window (Sep–Mar) and the test window (Mar–Apr), which trees cannot
extrapolate and which the target-mean features are biased against.

Two changes to attack this, plus the honest metric needed to tune them:

- src/model.py `time_holdout_validation`: an honest, leakage-free forecast
  validation. It holds out the last weeks of TRAIN as a pseudo-test and rebuilds
  the target-derived features (avg_bikes_per_station, tprof_*) from the earlier
  part only — the same shape as the real train->test gap — so it tracks the
  leaderboard, unlike the optimistic nested-CV whose features leak the target.

- src/model.py `recency_weights` + `sample_weight` in `train_final_model`:
  exponential-decay weights so recent rows count more, nudging the model's level
  toward the (higher) spring test period and reducing the under-prediction RMSLE
  punishes.

- src/data_cleaning.py: thread a `cache_dir` through clean_data /
  add_avg_bikes_per_station / add_target_profile_features so the validation can
  rebuild the target caches in a scratch dir without clobbering data/interim.
  The weather cache is exogenous (no leakage) and keeps its default location.

- notebooks/03_modeling.ipynb: stash the timestamps before they are dropped,
  add a RECENCY_HALFLIFE knob on the final fit, and add a cell that reports the
  honest holdout RMSLE across half-lives so the team can pick what actually
  helps before submitting.

